These are the interfaces we require to be implemented by each database driver library, for use by our library internally. Typical users will never use these interfaces directly. Driver libraries may provide different interfaces for their users to use directly, as long as they provide the "driver" export for compatibility.
All methods exist in async versions (with no suffix) and sync versions (with "Sync" suffix), omitted here for brevity. Most drivers will only implement the async versions.
